the-powder-toy (84.0-1~getdeb1) precise; urgency=low

  * New upstream version
    Version 84.0
    Fixed Can't undo ambient heat
    Fixed lag when deleting stamps, and the empty space left behind
    afterwards
    Fixed stamp thubnails take too long to load
    Fixed Can't reload or resave local saves easily
    Fixed Add a button to bring back missing stamps
    Fixed Fix being able to set an element's type to an invalid element with
    the console
    Changed Change the vote bars back to the old ones
    Added SIgns can link to forum threads. Use {t:id|sign text}, where id is
    the thread id
    Added New Element: DMG, Damage, generates a powerful force of pressure on
    contact with other elements
    Added New Element: TSNS, Temperature sensor, creates a spark when a
    nearby material has a greater temperature
    Added New Element: VIBR, solid material that stores massive amount of
    energy before going critical

    Version 83.7
    Fixed Prevents some freezes when browsing saves with a slow internet
    connection
    Changed Much faster gravity simulation
    Changed Moves to a C++ codebase.
    Added Ability to ignore update notifications
    Added Multiple save selection for mass deletion and favouring
    Added Right click menu for in save browser (Open, View History + more)
    Added Console remembers previous commands, event after closing
    Added New menu for decoration tools
    Added New decoration blending tools
    Added Video recording (Press R) uses PPM as an output format
    Added PNG format for screenshots (Press P to capture)
    Added New middle click tool (defaults to Sample tool)
    Added New Lua API
    Added Scollable comments in save preview

    Version 83.0
    Fixed Fix some elements melting when heat simulation is disabled
    Fixed PPIP glowing brick works even when "Glow" display mode is disabled.
    Changed tpt.element (Lua API) can now take an element number and return a
    name.
    Changed Corrected proportions of elements during some reactions with SPNG
    and GEL
    Added New Element: DTEC, generates a spark when something with it's ctype
    is nearby
    Added SPNG and GEL can draw moisture from other water based elements
    (Saltwater, etc)
    Added SPNG absorption limit (can be used as a filter for saltwater)

 -- Christoph Korn <christoph.korn@getdeb.net>  Fri, 09 Nov 2012 19:33:18 +0100

